{
  "stem": "12674.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were melting it down or whatever and stamping out new paper.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in order to get the-- the old paper into the factory, there were-- there were trucks and horse-drawn wagons sent out to the different places that had old paper to sell-- old business papers, stocks, and papers and old records and old books and things like that.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were usually kept in-- in cellars and downstairs or in back, you know, backrooms or back offices.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was assigned to a-- a horse-drawn wagon with two other Jewish girls.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were three of us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were to get the old paper, bring it onto the-- onto the-- the-- the wagon, you know, load it onto the wagon, where it was taken back to the factory and unloaded.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then they were doing-- they were sorting it and putting it [INAUDIBLE] with linen, without linen, cardboard, whatever.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I was there from August 19-- from August 1940-- because my mother was still alive.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I remember when I came back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I went home every night, until, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think, '42.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Yeah, sort of like September '42, something like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My job consisted out of put the-- we had these round baskets and-- or bales.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had like a stevedore's hook.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The bales were cardboard and cottons and things like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And loose papers, like letters and books and things, went in the baskets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And you had to carry the basket and hold it between your neck, behind your-- you know, over your shoulders and carry it up the stairs and then push it over the side of the wagon and drop it in there.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
